Consider the standard Java <i>cough</i> paradigm used by multitudes of developers, and on by default in many Java IDEs:<p><pre><code>    /* Gets the person's name
       @returns the person's name */
    public String getName() {
       return name;
    }
</code></pre>
That is insane. The comment adds nothing to anyone's day and helps no one better understand the method than after simply reading the method signature.
